The paper deals with the problem of recovering signals from compressed measurements, which is a common topic in the Information Theory (cs.IT), Signal Processing (cs.SP), and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a new concept of orthonormal atomic norm minimization, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and could potentially be of interest to researchers in that field. Finally, the paper provides a matrix-theoretic inequality of nuclear norm, which could be relevant to researchers in the Statistical Learning (cs.SI) sub-category.
